<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5105&amp;p=21821#p21821"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">GauravK wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Classic Shell does not modify this behavior of Explorer definitely. It can be a Windows 10 Explorer bug.<br /><br />When you set any sort order, open Folder Options from the View tab of the Ribbon from that folder and click &quot;Apply to folders&quot;. For all folders that use that template (there are 5 templates - Generic, Documents, Pictures, Music and Videos), the sort order *should* be remembered. See this article: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://winaero.com/blog/how-to-set-a-folder-view-in-explorer-for-all-folders-list-details-tiles-small-or-large-icons/">http://winaero.com/blog/how-to-set-a-fo ... rge-icons/</a><!-- m --> (How to set a folder view in Explorer for all folders). The rules for the sort order are the same as folder views.<br /></div><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />yes I kinda agree its not classical shell, but I cant think of anything else that can do this. I should be able to set any folder in any sort order that I want like I do with win 7. im going to try a clean install again...and the first thing im going to do is try to set the sort order for certain folders the way I want as well as set desktop icons to small. if it does not hold, then I would have to say its a bug in win 10 although this seems to only be happening to me.<br /><br />I made an image so I can put it back if need be.<br /><br /><br /><br />thanks for your reply<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=11325">yikes</a> — Sat Sep 05, 2015 2:54 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
