<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Weird problem on desktop and file explorer]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5105&amp;p=21789#p21789"><![CDATA[
Classic Shell does not modify this behavior of Explorer definitely. It can be a Windows 10 Explorer bug.<br /><br />When you set any sort order, open Folder Options from the View tab of the Ribbon from that folder and click &quot;Apply to folders&quot;. For all folders that use that template (there are 5 templates - Generic, Documents, Pictures, Music and Videos), the sort order *should* be remembered. See this article: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://winaero.com/blog/how-to-set-a-folder-view-in-explorer-for-all-folders-list-details-tiles-small-or-large-icons/">http://winaero.com/blog/how-to-set-a-fo ... rge-icons/</a><!-- m --> (How to set a folder view in Explorer for all folders). The rules for the sort order are the same as folder views.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Fri Sep 04, 2015 8:08 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
